The origin of this phrase is not known.

'''Proper use:'''

- I'm going to stick to you like white on rice

'''Improper use:'''

- That's as cool as white on rice

'''Sightings:'''

In the Ike & Tina Turner song "Baby Get It On", the following lyrics appear:

''Now you're the finest girl I ever saw in my life / ''
''I want to stick to you like white on rice / ''
''So come on.''

